description:
The Trio Wanderer performs a vocal and colourful interpretation of Haydn's 44th Piano Trio. This performance is somewhat faster than others, which gives the Trio much vigour and energy. Throughout the piece, the Trio Wanderer always have a wonderful and distinct sense of voice leading, so that the listener never feels lost as they listen. This piece was written in 1797, and is noted for its virtuosity.

00:00 - Allegro Moderato
06:56 - Allegretto
09:44 - Finale: Allegro

Performed by Trio Wanderer:
Jean-Marc Phillips-Varjabédian - Violin
Raphaël Pidoux - Cello
Vincent Coq - Piano
